description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated individual with an interest in healthcare science to become a member of our pharmacy team at Bronglais Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is permanent and full time 37.5 hours a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an exciting and unique opportunity for a pharmacy assistant to have a varied role. You will be helping to deliver a high quality pharmacy service to our patients by working within the dispensary, stores and distribution and ward based medicines management services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be offered a variety of experience and training within each area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working in a pharmacy is desirable and you will be required to have or be eligible to work towards an NVQ level 2 in Pharmacy Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to provide a high quality service to our patients and colleagues, the successful candidate must demonstrate excellent communication skills, good computer skills, attention to detail, ability to work efficiently, be proactive in their work and work well as a part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are also expected to partake in a weekend working and Bank Holiday rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Pharmacy team is forward thinking and continually strives to improve the delivery of patient focused pharmaceutical care and optimise the use of medicines within the Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 25.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
